d, or sometimes even predicted, by modified theories\nof gravity, that do not introduce any dark fluid. I illustrate possible\nsolutions to these problems with the modified theory of gravity MOND, which\ndeparts from Newtonian gravity for accelerations smaller than $a_0$, and with\nRefracted Gravity, a novel classical theory of gravity introduced in 2016,\nwhere the modification of the law of gravity is instead regulated by a density\nscale.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Jan 2023 19:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-19"}
